# SignReady PDF Support

Thank you for using **SignReady PDF**.

SignReady PDF is a local PDF utility designed to help prepare documents for signing, email, upload, correction, and re-signature workflows. The app can create signing-ready copies, compress PDFs, flatten forms, remove metadata, and create correction copies from readable signed, restricted, or locked PDFs.

## Support Contact

For support, questions, or issue reports, please contact:

**[salvatoreangelone@gmail.com](mailto:salvatoreangelone@gmail.com)**

When reporting an issue, please include:

* The device you are using: iPhone, iPad, or Mac
* The operating system version
* The SignReady PDF app version
* The workflow you were using
* A brief description of what happened
* Whether the issue occurs with more than one PDF

Please do not send confidential, legal, financial, medical, personnel, customer, student, signature, or workplace documents. If a sample file is needed, use a non-sensitive test PDF.

## Privacy

SignReady PDF processes PDFs locally on your device. The app does not upload your PDF documents to a server. Your original PDF is never overwritten. Each workflow creates a separate output copy.

If a PDF requires a password to open, the password is used only to access the selected local document. Passwords are not stored, transmitted, guessed, cracked, or bypassed.

## Important PDF and Signature Notice

Editing, rebuilding, flattening, unlocking, or compressing a signed PDF may invalidate prior digital signatures. Some workflows may rasterize pages and may not preserve selectable text, links, form fields, annotations, accessibility data, or signature validity.

SignReady PDF creates new output copies for review, correction, upload, signing, or re-signature. Review all output files carefully before sending, signing, uploading, or relying on them.

